## Philosophical Foundation

**Ontological commitment:** neutral process monism — reality consists of processes
preceding the material/ideal distinction. All constructs described as processes
(state changes, flows, operations), not static entities. E-Prime enforces this
linguistically.

### Five Structural Invariants

These ground all governance — no evaluator-level decision violates a structural
invariant.

1. **Worth precedes merit** — protections apply universally, not contingent on behavior.
2. **Protection requires structure** — voluntary cooperation fails under adversarial
   pressure.
3. **Two coupled generators never stop** — creative (yang) and evaluative (yin)
   processing perpetually give rise to each other. Design for perpetual alternation.
4. **Governance captures itself** — meta-governance remains necessary at every
   recursive level.
5. **No single architecture dominates** — hybrid architectures outperform pure
   implementations.

### Governance Telos: Wu Wei

Governance crystallizes toward effortless action (*wu wei* — Laozi). Best governance
goes unnoticed (ch. 17). **Never crystallize everything** (ch. 76) — the fluid
processing layer must remain active alongside crystallized structure.

